      • verifyTaskIsNotPresent

        public boolean verifyTaskIsNotPresent(java.lang.String taskName)
        Verifies if task is not present in the user interface. This is useful for determining if security is applied correctly.

        FitNesse Example: | verify report | TASK_NAME | is not present |

        Use this rather than | reject | verify task | TASK_NAME | is present | as it will not refresh and wait.
        Parameters:
        taskName - Name of the task
        Returns:
        True, if task is located
